    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix F1AP Setup Response Equality Check and Related Functions\n\n### Summary\nThe `eq_f1ap_setup_response()` function and related equality/copy functions in the F1AP interface management library were not properly handling `SI_container` comparisons and copies. This caused incorrect behavior when comparing F1AP messages with system information containers.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_interface_management.c`: \n  - Fixed `eq_f1ap_setup_response()` to properly compare `SI_container` content using `memcmp` instead of incorrect pointer dereferencing\n  - Fixed `eq_f1ap_cu_configuration_update()` with same `SI_container` comparison fix\n  - Fixed `eq_f1ap_du_configuration_update_acknowledge()` with same `SI_container` comparison fix\n  - Fixed `eq_f1ap_setup_request()` by removing redundant array size check\n  - Fixed `cp_f1ap_setup_response()` to properly copy `SI_container` content using `memcpy`\n  - Fixed `cp_f1ap_cu_configuration_update()` with same `SI_container` copy fix\n  - Fixed `cp_f1ap_du_configuration_update_acknowledge()` with same `SI_container` copy fix\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `eq_f1ap_setup_response()` with two `f1ap_setup_resp_t` structures that contain identical system information containers, the function would incorrectly return `false` due to improper pointer comparison instead of content comparison. This could lead to:\n- Unnecessary retransmissions of F1 Setup Response messages\n- Incorrect message handling in F1AP state machines\n- Potential memory access violations when dereferencing invalid pointers\n\nThe issue is particularly evident when the F1AP stack attempts to verify received Setup Response messages against expected values, causing the gNB-DU to incorrectly reject valid Setup Responses from the gNB-CU.\n"
}